projects.title: Low Heat Loss Transformer
projects.description: Power transformer with improved heat losses relative to a standard iron core transformer. Cost and time to delivery are also critical. See attached documents for detailed specs. Evaluator Service encompasses how the trade-offs will be valued among heat loss, cost, and delivery time.

services.title: micro Fuel Cell
services.description: A  service to model the lifespan of a micro fuel cell for small cells that use  alcohol to convert  chemical energy  into electrical energy. Commonly used in cell phones or edge devices for M2M  communications.

services.title: Computer Aided Manufacturing
services.description: Develop computer software to control machine tools and related machinery in the manufacturing of workpieces. This service will easily convert your CAM model into simple file of G-codes/M-Codes for downloading to your CNC machine.

services.title: Biological Oxygen Demand
services.description:
Biochemical oxygen demand (BOD) is the amount of dissolved oxygen used by microorganisms in the biological process of metabolizing organic matter in water. This service allows you to input the amount of organic matter in your system and will
  output the level of organic pollution of a body of water.

services.title: Plasticity

discussions.text: I just submitted the latest PLC code to the repository
Hey Peter, I'm having a heck of a time finding a transformer with the heat loss requirements we have
I am certain we will need to be creative building this transformer.  COTS is not going to cut it.
maybe we can use one of those collaborative sites and get a new design that will stay in-line with the customers expectations of cost
I will try to get some external bids for this work.
great, install them as soon as schedule permits
ok - after I run the service models for layout
Hey Peter, I'm having a heck of a time finding a transformer with the heat loss requirements we have
I am certain we will need to be creative building this transformer.  COTS is not going to cut it.
maybe we can use one of those collaborative sites and get some good designs
I'll take care of this.  Leave it to me
the new mtl we have developed should work in the transformer core
I agree, we just have to determine what mtl parameters we need
yes, and how they impact transformer performance and heat loss
OK, let me investigate; I'll look for a relevant magnetic permeability model
